making that decision.

13
00:00:30,650 --> 00:00:33,739
And often we think of it
as the selection process,

14
00:00:33,740 --> 00:00:36,760
but really right now it's
almost the elimination process.

15
00:00:36,760 --> 00:00:39,390
Because you generally have a lot
more unsuccessful applicants,

16
00:00:39,390 --> 00:00:41,460
than you do have
successful applicants.

17
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:44,480
So as we go through
we'll look at one way

18
00:00:44,480 --> 00:00:47,690
we can really try
and select people

19
00:00:47,690 --> 00:00:49,669
in a more systematic way.

20
00:00:49,670 --> 00:00:54,630
And one such technique is really
breaking it down into a scale.

21
00:00:54,630 --> 00:00:58,840
So gathering the remaining
candidates that we think yes,

22
00:00:58,840 --> 00:01:02,020
they may have potential to
be the perfect candidate

23
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:03,450
for this particular job.

24
00:01:03,450 --> 00:01:07,270
And let's try and match up their
skills, their qualifications,

25
00:01:07,270 --> 00:01:09,750
the information we've
gathered during interviews,

26
00:01:09,750 --> 00:01:12,510
and really rate them
based on a scale.

27
00:01:12,510 --> 00:01:14,650
And this is just an
example of one scale.

28
00:01:14,650 --> 00:01:17,370
So we right one particularly
candidate as an A,

29
00:01:17,370 --> 00:01:22,050
because they seem to have met
almost all of the requirements,

30
00:01:22,050 --> 00:01:24,420
and they seem to have
ticked off all of the boxes.

31
00:01:24,420 --> 00:01:25,710
And then we keep going down.

32
00:01:25,710 --> 00:01:29,410
B, yep, not too bad, acceptable,
they have confidence.

33
00:01:29,410 --> 00:01:31,300
C, yes they're satisfactory.

34
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:34,024
And then you may not
have many in the D and E

35
00:01:34,025 --> 00:01:36,650
stage because you probably would
have filtered them out by now.

36
00:01:36,650 --> 00:01:41,110
But it really tries to, I
guess almost prioritize what's

37
00:01:41,110 --> 00:01:42,380
remaining of the candidates.

38
00:01:42,380 --> 00:01:45,259
And help you get an idea
of what you can-- really

39
00:01:45,260 --> 00:01:48,250
of what you can be looking
for in that final candidate.

40
